    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 220&deg;C/ 200&deg;C (fan)/ 425&deg;F/ Gas 7</p> <p>Boil a kettle, then drain and rinse the&nbsp;<strong>kidney beans</strong></p> <p>Add the&nbsp;<strong>kidney beans</strong>&nbsp;to a baking tray with a small drizzle of&nbsp;<strong>olive oil</strong>&nbsp;and a pinch of&nbsp;<strong>salt</strong>&nbsp;and&nbsp;<strong>pepper</strong></p> <p>Give everything a good mix up and put them in the oven for 20-25 min or until the skins have burst and are crispy</p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/mexican-pork-and-popped-bean-bowl/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, peel and grate the <strong>garlic</strong></p> <p>Combine the <strong>ground&nbsp;turmeric</strong>, <strong>natural yoghurt</strong> and<strong> grated garlic</strong> in a small bowl with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong>&nbsp;&ndash; this is your <strong>turmeric yoghurt</strong></p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/mexican-pork-and-popped-bean-bowl/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>bulgur wheat</strong> to a pot with plenty of <strong>boiled water</strong> and a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> (the same as you would for pasta) and cook over a high heat for 10-15 min or until tender with a slight bite, then drain and return to the pot</p> <p>Re-boil a kettle</p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/mexican-pork-and-popped-bean-bowl/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Cut the&nbsp;<strong>cucumber&nbsp;</strong>in half lengthways and scrape out the inner seeds with a teaspoon,&nbsp;discarding the seeds</p> <p>Grate the&nbsp;<strong>cucumber&nbsp;</strong><br /><br />Slice the&nbsp;<strong>cherry&nbsp;tomatoes</strong> in half</p> <p>Chop the <strong>coriander</strong> finely, including the stalks</p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/mexican-pork-and-popped-bean-bowl/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Add the&nbsp;<strong>chopped tomatoes, coriander </strong>and&nbsp;<strong>cucumber</strong>&nbsp;to a bowl</p> <p>Add the juice of 1/2&nbsp;<span class=\"text-danger\">[1]</span>&nbsp;<strong>lime</strong>&nbsp;and season with a pinch of&nbsp;<strong>salt</strong>&nbsp;&ndash; this is your&nbsp;<strong>cucumber salsa</strong>&nbsp;</p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/mexican-pork-and-popped-bean-bowl/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a drizzle of <strong>olive oil</strong> over a medium heat</p> <p>Add the <strong>diced pork</strong> with the <strong>ground cumin,</strong>&nbsp;<strong>smoked paprika</strong>&nbsp;and a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and cook for 3-4 min or until browned all over</p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/mexican-pork-and-popped-bean-bowl/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once the pork has browned, add the <strong>tomato paste</strong>&nbsp;with 50ml <span class=\"text-danger\">[100ml]</span><strong> boiled water</strong> and cook for 2 min further or until a thick sauce has formed<strong>&nbsp;</strong>&ndash;<strong>&nbsp;</strong>this is your<strong> Mexican pork</strong></p> <p>Meanwhile, cut the remaining<strong> lime </strong>into wedges</p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/mexican-pork-and-popped-bean-bowl/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Serve the<strong> Mexican pork</strong> over the <strong>cooked bulgur wheat</strong> with the<strong> cucumber salsa</strong>, <strong>popped beans</strong>&nbsp;and&nbsp;<strong>turmeric yoghurt</strong>&nbsp;to the side</p> <p>Garnish with a wedge of <strong>lime</strong></p> <p>Enjoy!</p>",
            "order": 8
        }
